Seven Years After S.C.O.T.U.S. Decided Gay Marriage Was A "Constitutional Right" In 'Obergefell v. Hodges', America's Judicial System Still Struggles With The Question On Whether Small Businesses, Particularly Bakeries And Flower Shops Must Necessarily Provide Services To Unions Whose Personal Conduct Contradict The Owners' Religious Beliefs.

In Kern County, California Superior Court, Religious Liberty Gained A Victory.

The Associated Press, And The 'Bakersfield Californian' Newspaper Said Judge Eric Bradshaw Ruled A Bakersfield Bakery Owner Who Declined To Make A Wedding Cake For A Lesbian Couple, But Instead Referred Said Couple To Another Baker Was Not Violating The Stateâ€™s Civil Rights Statutes Because She Was Acting In Accordance With Her Belief In Biblical Principles.

The Stateâ€™s Department Of Fair Housing & Employment Sued Cathy Miller, Owner Of 'Tastries Bakery', Claiming Her Refusal Violated California's Civil Rights Act.

...â€œMillerâ€™s Only Motivation Was To Act
